<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: how to create wifi hotspot in parrot 3.6</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>I take you don&#039; t want to create an &#039;evil twin&#039; but a hotspot for other computers to share, right? (And maybe listen on it since we are all pentesters, right? Ahem).</p><p>In that case:<br/>*Create a new wifi-network<br/>* Go to &#039;edit connections&#039;. Select: Mode ===&gt; ad hoc<br/>* Wifi security tab: Select whatever security or none<br/>* Tab IP4 Settings: Method &quot;shared to other computes&quot; <br/>*IP6 Settings: Set as &#039;ignore&#039;</p><p>You&#039; re all set.<br/>Now if you want to connect left click on the connections icon on the panel and select &#039;connect to hidden Wi-Fi network and select the connection you just created. Your laptop is now a &#039;hotspot&#039; and the active connection should be in the network list, just check.</p>
</div>
<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr/><p>Encourage and teach others to be better at Linux stuff. Don&#039;t talk &#039;em down but help them. We are all in the same boat.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
