<h3>Re: how to create wifi hotspot in parrot 3.6</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<div class="quotebox"><cite>Michael Brahms wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>I take you don&#039; t want to create an &#039;evil twin&#039; but a hotspot for other computers to share, right? (And maybe listen on it since we are all pentesters, right? Ahem).</p><p>In that case:<br/>*Create a new wifi-network<br/>* Go to &#039;edit connections&#039;. Select: Mode ===&gt; ad hoc<br/>* Wifi security tab: Select whatever security or none<br/>* Tab IP4 Settings: Method &quot;shared to other computes&quot; <br/>*IP6 Settings: Set as &#039;ignore&#039;</p><p>You&#039; re all set.<br/>Now if you want to connect left click on the connections icon on the panel and select &#039;connect to hidden Wi-Fi network and select the connection you just created. Your laptop is now a &#039;hotspot&#039; and the active connection should be in the network list, just check.</p></div></blockquote></div><br/><p>Yeah just a standard hotspot like you create on a windows pc to share connection to your other devices. but i cannot do so.&#160; <br/>steps i have followed:<br/>1) create new connection.<br/>2) give it a name ,ssid , mode = hotspot , band = automatic, device =&#160; wlan. the rest default.<br/>3) security = wpa personal, <br/>4) proxy none.<br/>5) ip4 = shared to others , ip6 = ignore</p><p>cant see on my devices.<br/>if i see the created hotspot on my devices , it connects but there is no internet access.</p>
