<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: how to create wifi hotspot in parrot 3.6</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<div class="quotebox"><blockquote><div><p>give it a name ,ssid , mode = hotspot , band = automatic, device =&#160; wlan. the rest default.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>Change &quot;mode=hotspot&#039;&#160; to &quot;mode=AD HOC&quot; as explained and you&#039;ll be all set. For some reason hotspot doesn&#039;t work. It would work by installing some 3rd party software to create a hotspot but doing so would compromise your installation so I advice against that.</p>
</div>
<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr/><p>Encourage and teach others to be better at Linux stuff. Don&#039;t talk &#039;em down but help them. We are all in the same boat.</p></div>
</div>
