<div class="postright">
<h3>Re: how to create wifi hotspot in parrot 3.6</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<div class="quotebox"><blockquote><div><p>if i see the created hotspot on my devices , it connects but there is no internet access.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>That is correct. Your local machine acts as an Access Point so locally you will have no internet on that machine. Since your laptop is now an AP you need to connect other devices to that machine. Like a phone or other laptop. You just created an entirely new network with your laptop as the router/modem to say simplified.</p>
</div>
<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr/><p>Encourage and teach others to be better at Linux stuff. Don&#039;t talk &#039;em down but help them. We are all in the same boat.</p></div>
</div>
